[
    {
        "text": "There had been a polio outbreak recently in Borno.",
        "start": 1.24,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "In two years there hadn't been a case.",
        "start": 4.78,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Everyone thought Polio was gone.",
        "start": 7.02,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "I was actually following up on the Polio situation",
        "start": 8.78,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "and started seeing reports from the Borno government",
        "start": 11.9,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "and others that this huge crisis was underway",
        "start": 15.0,
        "duration": 3.26
    },
    {
        "text": "and everybody knew Boko Haram was there",
        "start": 18.7,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "and committed terrible atrocities but no one knew",
        "start": 21.46,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "how many people had been trapped",
        "start": 24.74,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "living under Boko Haram control.",
        "start": 26.72,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "The army came in and started liberating areas.",
        "start": 28.52,
        "duration": 3.4
    },
    {
        "text": "That's when they realized that there were millions",
        "start": 32.28,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "of people who had been deprived of everything",
        "start": 35.16,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "for about five or eight years.",
        "start": 38.96,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Almost two million people have been displaced",
        "start": 41.84,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "and they're crowding into camps that can't",
        "start": 45.66,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "accommodate them and communities that are so poor",
        "start": 48.2,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "that they can't feed themselves in the first place.",
        "start": 51.64,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 53.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 55.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 57.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 59.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 61.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 63.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "The UN estimates that without",
        "start": 65.92,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Polio essentially is a sign that the",
        "start": 73.12,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "health system has collapsed",
        "start": 75.48,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Malaria--child mortality  was off the charts",
        "start": 77.56,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "And a measles outbreak",
        "start": 81.06,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "I was horrified by the combination",
        "start": 83.06,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "My name is Leslie Roberts",
        "start": 96.7,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "and I'm a deputy news editor at Science Magazine",
        "start": 98.84,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "I went to northern Nigeria",
        "start": 101.96,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "to look at this humanitarian crisis",
        "start": 103.58,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "with support from the",
        "start": 105.56,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "Pulitzer Center on Crisis Reporting",
        "start": 107.28,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "The worst of the crisis is concentrated",
        "start": 109.86,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "in Borno",
        "start": 112.42,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "We visited Maiduguri",
        "start": 113.68,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "The first thing we did was go to the feeding center",
        "start": 116.9,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "It was in a courtyard",
        "start": 119.86,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "with lots of women with their children",
        "start": 121.7,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "waiting and these are kids who",
        "start": 124.82,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "had already been screened",
        "start": 127.26,
        "duration": 2.02
    },
    {
        "text": "and they had severe acute malnutrition",
        "start": 129.32,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "which is the worst kind",
        "start": 131.8,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "and if you're not treated, 1 in 5 dies",
        "start": 133.6,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "But these kids were already on treatment",
        "start": 136.1,
        "duration": 3.62
    },
    {
        "text": "They're getting ready to eat therapeutic food",
        "start": 140.12,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "then they would measure the kid's arm",
        "start": 142.74,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "to see if they were recovering",
        "start": 145.3,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "Malnutrition is bad enough in itself",
        "start": 148.32,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "and then it suppresses the immune system",
        "start": 152.1,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "so when you get these infections",
        "start": 155.3,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "a severely malnourished child",
        "start": 157.34,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "is 9 times more likely to die",
        "start": 159.68,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "The next day we took the UN helicopter to Monguno",
        "start": 162.86,
        "duration": 4.74
    },
    {
        "text": "in the very north east corner of the state",
        "start": 167.86,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "which has only been open",
        "start": 170.66,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "for about 6 months",
        "start": 172.52,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "the areas around it",
        "start": 174.38,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "are still under Boko Haram control",
        "start": 176.84,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "And the conditions here are even worse",
        "start": 179.08,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "than in Maiduguri",
        "start": 182.24,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "We went to a UNICEF clinic",
        "start": 183.62,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "And the health worker would ask:",
        "start": 186.76,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "How long has your kid been sick?",
        "start": 189.1,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "What are the symptoms?",
        "start": 190.86,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "The kid would have fever and cough",
        "start": 192.42,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "Ordinarily you use a rapid diagnostic test",
        "start": 194.66,
        "duration": 2.36
    },
    {
        "text": "which is the finger prick of blood",
        "start": 197.28,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "but hers had expired",
        "start": 199.46,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "so she had no choice but to treat everybody",
        "start": 201.94,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "as if they had malaria",
        "start": 205.04,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "We went to that transit post",
        "start": 208.18,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "This is something that the polio eradication initiative",
        "start": 210.58,
        "duration": 4.18
    },
    {
        "text": "has started fairly recently",
        "start": 214.86,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "They usually go door-to-door",
        "start": 216.84,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "to vaccinate kids",
        "start": 218.82,
        "duration": 0.94
    },
    {
        "text": "But in Nigerian is this crisis",
        "start": 219.94,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "so many people are on the move",
        "start": 222.06,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "They find that they're missing a lot of kids",
        "start": 223.6,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "So they select, in this case it's a road",
        "start": 225.64,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "that goes between two areas",
        "start": 228.6,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "that are inaccessible",
        "start": 231.54,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "under Boko Haram control",
        "start": 233.16,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "and also heads into Maiduguri",
        "start": 234.78,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "(the capital)",
        "start": 237.5,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "So they could get people fleeing Boko Haram",
        "start": 238.8,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "They could get nomads",
        "start": 241.84,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Anytime a woman goes by with a child",
        "start": 243.52,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "They flag her over",
        "start": 246.68,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "and see if the child has been vaccinated",
        "start": 248.66,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "and if not, vaccinate the child",
        "start": 251.26,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "One young doctor took us to the measles ward",
        "start": 255.4,
        "duration": 3.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Nobody knows exactly how many kids are affected",
        "start": 259.28,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "but he was saying:",
        "start": 262.74,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't need lab confirmations",
        "start": 263.92,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "this is huge",
        "start": 265.68,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "He's seeing more than 40 kids a week",
        "start": 267.42,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "First they have the rash",
        "start": 271.36,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "The kids have conjunctivitis--",
        "start": 273.52,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "their eyes are swollen",
        "start": 275.96,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "and if it's not treated and can lead to blindness",
        "start": 277.78,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "A lot have respiratory infections",
        "start": 281.1,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "And there were kids who had to be on oxygen",
        "start": 284.32,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Other kids have diarrhea that so bad",
        "start": 288.1,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "they're on IVs",
        "start": 291.22,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Some of the children have sores in their mouth",
        "start": 292.72,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "So they can't eat",
        "start": 295.54,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "which exacerbates malnutrition",
        "start": 296.66,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "In a developing country, without a crisis",
        "start": 299.12,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "you'd see about 2% mortality",
        "start": 301.78,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "In disasters like this, you see 10%",
        "start": 303.96,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "sometimes even 30%",
        "start": 307.32,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "There are easy fixes",
        "start": 311.9,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "for a lot of these problems",
        "start": 313.6,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "The biggest need is really the screen for malnutrition",
        "start": 315.64,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "and treating these kids with food",
        "start": 319.5,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "The army, the air force",
        "start": 321.18,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "have to continue their fight",
        "start": 323.26,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "And then more money",
        "start": 324.98,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "more aid groups, relief groups",
        "start": 327.28,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "need to get in and need to get access",
        "start": 329.56,
        "duration": 2.68
    },
    {
        "text": "But the scale is so big",
        "start": 332.78,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "and so many are inaccessible still",
        "start": 335.0,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "To talk to people about what had happened to them",
        "start": 337.48,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "it was devastating",
        "start": 340.72,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "They all had tales of children they'd lost",
        "start": 343.24,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "or husbands had been murdered",
        "start": 347.22,
        "duration": 2.68
    },
    {
        "text": "And it just seems so appalling",
        "start": 350.5,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "that nothing had been done",
        "start": 353.46,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Nobody--it's this forgotten place",
        "start": 355.34,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Part of it is there are so many crises",
        "start": 358.08,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "all over the world right now",
        "start": 360.6,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "That they're all vying for the same pot of money",
        "start": 362.2,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "But for some reason Nigeria seems to be",
        "start": 364.76,
        "duration": 3.3
    },
    {
        "text": "at the bottom of the list",
        "start": 368.06,
        "duration": 2.26
    }
]